# ghbackup-crontab.sample — example crontab entries for the two mirrors
# maintained on this machine. Install with `crontab -e` and paste whichever
# lines you want active; edit the absolute paths and schedules to taste.
#
# Both entries use --quiet + --lock-file so:
#   • cron only emails you on actual failures (ghbackup exits non-zero),
#   • overlapping runs no-op cleanly instead of stacking up mirrors.
#
# macOS note: on Catalina+, cron needs Full Disk Access for your user's
# `cron` process in System Settings → Privacy & Security → Full Disk Access,
# otherwise mounted-volume writes silently fail.
#
# Paths below assume the repo is checked out at the hard-coded location
# used on this machine; adjust PROTOREPO if yours differs.

PROTOREPO=/Volumes/wd_office_1/repos/proto-repo

# Daily at 02:30 — mirror everything under the accretional org.
30 2 * * * $PROTOREPO/ghbackup-cron.sh --owner accretional --dest /Volumes/wd_office_1/backup/repos --quiet --lock-file /tmp/ghbackup-accretional.lock

# Weekly on Sunday at 03:15 — refresh the curated third-party protobuf list.
15 3 * * 0 $PROTOREPO/ghbackup-cron.sh --list-file /Volumes/wd_office_1/third_party/repos.txt --dest /Volumes/wd_office_1/third_party --quiet --lock-file /tmp/ghbackup-third-party.lock
